I've had two HP Pavilion gaming laptops. The first one was fixed twice under warranty for pixel failure. This occurred a third time - out of warranty - and then the keyboard died. I gave up and bought another one because I was able to stack a few discounts together and it came in very cheap for the specs and thought I must have just been unlucky.This next one  lasted all of 3 months before being back to the service centre for--pixel failure. I found HP's customer service to be torturous to deal with. I still quite like it. It looks nice, has a great keyboard and runs games very well. I don't honestly think it would survive many trips to clients' offices though,  no matter how many ports it has Pretty much everything flexes if you squeeze it and the trackpad is now loose. I  wonder how long that wobbly Victus screen will actually last. Sometimes, things being cheap comes with a cost. I will probably look at Asus next time as they seem to be pretty solid.
